<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<worksheet>
  <title>Section 2.3 - The Span of a Set of Vectors</title>
  <objectives>
    <ul>
      <li><p>What is the span of a set of vectors and how do we denote it?</p></li>
      <li><p>How can we determine if a vector is in the span of another set of vectors?</p></li>
      <li><p>How do we know if the span of a set of vectors <m>\vvec_1, \vvec_2, \dots, \vvec_n</m> is <m>\mathbb{R}^m</m> using the pivots of the matrix <m>[\vvec_1 \vvec_2 \vvec_3 \dots \vvec_n]</m>?</p></li>
    </ul>
  </objectives>

  <exercise>
    <introduction>
      <p>Let's start in 2-dimensions, and suppose that   
<md>
  \vvec_1=\twovec11,~~~
  \vvec_2=\twovec{-3}{-3},~~~
  \vvec_3=\twovec14.
  </md></p>
    </introduction>
    <task workspace="1in">
      <statement>
        <p>Is <m>\twovec66</m> in the span of <m>\vvec_1</m> and <m>\vvec_2</m>?</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
    <task workspace="1in">
      <statement>
        <p>Is <m>\twovec45</m> in the span of <m>\vvec_1</m> and <m>\vvec_2</m>?</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
    <task workspace="1in">
      <statement>
        <p>Give a geometric description of the span of <m>\vvec_1</m> and <m>\vvec_2</m>, denoted <m>\span{\vvec_1,\vvec_2}</m>.</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
    <task workspace="1in">
      <statement>
        <p>Can <m>\twovec45</m> be expressed as a linear combination of <m>\vvec_1</m> and <m>\vvec_3</m>?  Is <m>\twovec45</m> in the span of <m>\vvec_1</m> and <m>\vvec_3</m>?</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
    <task workspace="1in">
      <statement>
        <p>Give a geometric description of the span of <m>\vvec_1</m> and <m>\vvec_3</m>.</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
    <task workspace="1in">
      <statement>
        <p>For what vectors <m>\bvec</m> does the equation \ \ \ \
  <m>
  \begin{bmatrix}
    1 \amp 1 \\
    1 \amp 4 \\
  \end{bmatrix} \xvec = \bvec
  </m> \ \ \ \ 
  have a solution?  Explain your thinking.</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
  </exercise>

  <exercise>
    <introduction>
      <p>Now we'll look at the span of sets of vectors in <m>\real^3</m>.</p>
    </introduction>
    <task workspace="1in">
      <statement>
        <p>Consider the vector <m>\vvec =\threevec121</m>.  Give a geometric
  description of <m>\laspan\{\vvec\}</m> and a rough sketch of the span
  below.</p>
        <p>\includegraphics[scale=.9]{coordinates-3d}</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
    <task workspace="1in">
      <statement>
        <p>Now consider the vectors
  <md>
  \evec_1 = \threevec100,~~~
  \evec_2 = \threevec010.
  </md>
  Give a geometric description of <m>\laspan\{\evec_1,\evec_2\}</m> and a
  rough sketch of the span below.</p>
        <p>\includegraphics[scale=.9]{coordinates-3d}</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
    <task workspace="1in">
      <statement>
        <p>Let's look at this situation algebraically.  If we write
  <m>\bvec=\threevec{b_1}{b_2}{b_3}</m>, what condition on the components
  of <m>\bvec</m> must be satisfied if the equation
  <md>
  \begin{bmatrix}
    1 \amp 0 \\
    0 \amp 1 \\
    0 \amp 0 \\
  \end{bmatrix}
  \xvec = \bvec
  </md>
  is consistent?  What condition on the components of <m>\bvec</m> must be
  satisfied for <m>\bvec</m> to be in the span of <m>\evec_1</m> and <m>\evec_2</m>?</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
  </exercise>

  <exercise>
    <introduction>
      <p>Consider the vectors
  <md>
  \vvec_1 = \threevec11{-1},~~~
  \vvec_2 = \threevec021,~~~
  \vvec_3 = \threevec1{-2}4.
  </md></p>
    </introduction>
    <task workspace="1in">
      <statement>
        <p>Is the vector <m>\threevec4{-3}{-1}</m> in
  <m>\laspan\{\vvec_1,\vvec_2,\vvec_3\}</m>?</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
    <task workspace="1in">
      <statement>
        <p>What is the reduced row echelon form of the matrix
  <m>\begin{bmatrix}
    \vvec_1 \amp \vvec_2 \amp \vvec_3
  \end{bmatrix}
  </m>?  You should be able to find this using your work from the last
  question.</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
    <task workspace="1in">
      <statement>
        <p>What do the pivot positions of this matrix tell you about
  <m>\laspan\{\vvec_1,\vvec_2,\vvec_3\}</m>?  Give a geometric description
  of <m>\laspan\{\vvec_1,\vvec_2,\vvec_3\}</m>.</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
  </exercise>

</worksheet>
